<div class="bore"><div class="alert alert-info"><b>In a nutshell circuits allow you to share cool lists of routes with your friends and the climbing community.</b></div></div>

<h2><a name="features">Features</a></h2>

<ul>
  <li>Share a themed list of routes</li>
  <li>Target routes for a trip</li>
  <li>Publish your lists</li>
  <li>Tick direct from circuit</li>
  <li>One click from your dashboard</li>
</ul>


%# <p>Examples:</p>
%# <ul>
%#   <li><em>Road to kachoong</em>: xxxx</li>
%#   <li><em>Arapiles ladder of classics</em>: xxxx</li>
%#   <li><em>Cool onsights in Arapiles</em>: xxxx</li>
%# </ul>


%#<p>You may be planning a trip and want to share your target routes with friends who are coming.</p>
%#<p>Got an idea for a good list of climbs, create an share the list for an area.</p>
%#<p>You want to list training routes for a session at a cliff or boulder. You can tick directly from the circuit, which makes for less mouse clicks.</p>
%#<p>Your stared circuits are one click away from your dashboard.</p>

<h2><a name="howto">How to</a></h2>

<h3>Create a circuit</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-01.png" width="300" height="209" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Go to the crag/area where you want to create the circuit.</p>
<p>Click on the 'Action->Create circuit' button.</p>
<p>Create your cool name and brief description.</p>
<p>Press save and the circuit is now stored in the crag/area as well as becoming your active editing circuit for adding routes.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Add route to a circuit</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-02.png" width="300" height="110" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Browse the index until you see the routes listed in the route table in an area.</p>
<p>On the popup Edit button associated with the route entry click the dropdown and then the "Add route to active circuit" link.</p>
<p>Note that your active circuit is the one you last added, or manually set as active by editing the circuit.</p>
<p>Alternatively do a route faceted search and do the same from the Action dropdown on the route entry.</p>
<p>Or even go to the route page and do it from there.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Find circuits in an area</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-03.png" width="300" height="80" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Browse the index list view to a particular crag.</p>
<p>Near the crag/area title there will be some statistics. The number of circuits for the area will be shown if there are any.</p>
<p>Click on the linked number to see the circuits for the crag.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Star circuits</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-04.png" width="300" height="112" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Starring a circuit puts it on your personal list of circuits which you can access from your dashboard.</p>
<p>Note that you can star anybodies circuits.</p>
<p>To star a circuit, find the circuit in circuits faceted search and click the hollow star image.</p>
<p>Starred circuits will have a full color star image (note you can also unstar by clicking this).</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Your stared circuits from your dashboard</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-05.png" width="300" height="79" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Go to your dashboard.</p>
<p>Click the Circuit button to get a list of your stared circuits.</p>
<p>This will take you to a list of circuits starred by you.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Circuits you created</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-06.png" width="300" height="138" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Go to your dashboard.</p>
<p>Click the 'Action -> Circuits created by you' link.</p>
<p>This will take you to a list of circuits created by you.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>See the list of routes in a circuit</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-07.png" width="300" height="78" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>From your list of ciruits click the circuit name.</p>
<p>This will take you to the list of routes for that circuit.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Tick from a circuit</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-08.png" width="300" height="66" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>From the circuit list of routes click the 'Action -> Log ascent'.</p>
<p>This will take you to the log ascent form.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Friends circuits</h3>

<table class="imagetext">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
<img src="/static/cids/images/circuit-1.1.0/Circuit-09.png" width="180" height="343" />
      </td>
      <td>
<p>Go to your circuits facetted search.</p>
<p>Open 'Created by' facet (note that you may have to close other facets)</p>
<p>Select the friend you want to follow.</p>
<p>Click Apply filters.</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
